problem_data.title: Number of Longest Increasing Subsequence
problem_data.description:
Given an integer array nums, return the number of longest increasing subsequences.

Notice that the sequence has to be strictly increasing.

examples.explanation: The two longest increasing subsequences are [1, 3, 4, 7] and [1, 3, 5, 7].
TThe length of the longest increasing subsequence is 1, and there are 5 increasing subsequences of length 1, so output 5.
